<para>You can easily use different layouts for different pages in your document.  Declare each different layout as a &lt;pageTemplate&gt; with an id in the &lt;template&gt; section.  Normally, the flowables will fill up the frames on a page and then flow into a new page with the same layout.  However, you can set the layout of the next page using the &lt;setNextTemplate name="templateID"/&gt; tag.  This will ensure that once the current page is full, the next page will have the layout specified.</para>

		
		

		
